[Humans may develop localized cutaneous lesions (malignant carbuncle) from
contact of broken skin with infected blood or tissues, or acquire a highly
fatal hemorrhagic mediastinitis (woolsorters' disease) from spore
inhalation when handling contaminated wool or hair. Man may also acquire
intestinal anthrax from consumption of under cooked meat. - Mod.TG
